text: KSKL (94.5 FM) is a radio station licensed to serve the community of Scott City, Kansas. The station is owned by Mark Yearout, through licensee Southwind Broadcasting, LLC, and airs an adult contemporary format. The station was assigned the call sign KFLA-FM by the Federal Communications Commission on June 7, 1965. The station changed its call sign to KULL on December 1, 1976, to KEZU on August 1, 1983, and to KSKL on March 30, 1990. ==References== ==External links== * Official Website * FCC Public Inspection File for KSKL * FCC History Card for KSKL * SKL Category:Radio stations established in 1965 Category:1965 establishments in Kansas Category:Adult contemporary radio stations in the United States Category:Scott County, Kansas
